## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

Creating the three main features of the game: the bricks, the paddle, and the ball.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

Creating multiple levels that increase in difficulty after each level is completed (adding obstacles), and adding lives.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

Implementing elements like changing the speed at the ball at different times, creating power-ups to aid the player in winning, inlcuding a high score, including a winning and losing screen.

## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?

I will first download Pygame and figure out its basic features and practice using it. I will research how to create games using Pygame, and I begin to try to use these new skills to figure out the more basic features of the game. I will learn how to code the graphics, and once I have a basic idea down of how to use Pygame, I will start by coding the three basic features, which are the ball, bricks, and paddle. I will have to figure out how to create graphics for these and how to get the player to control the paddle. Once the basic game is coded, I could then move on to adding in some of the more diffcult elements to code, such as obstacles, powerups, etc.
